-- Suntech CEO King Assumes CFO Duties as Interim CFO Steps Down
-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 2012-10-10T20:46:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-10/suntech-ceo-king-assumes-cfo-duties-as-interim-cfo-steps-down.html
Suntech Power Holdings Co., the
largest solar-panel maker, said its interim chief financial
officer stepped down from the top financial position “for
personal reasons.”  Anlin Ting-Mason will retain her position as CFO of the
Wuxi, China-based company’s U.S. unit, Suntech said in a filing
today.  David King , Suntech’s chief executive officer, will
assume the CFO duties while the company seeks a permanent
replacement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  